Optimize time lag & moving average window

Mikaela M. Provost

8/6/2020

Plan

  1. For each site, apply a large window moving average to get seasonal variation to raw SST and bottom data.
  2. Identify the time lag that minimizes r^2.
  3. Using the time lag identified in step 2, calculate r^2 for a variety of small moving average windows (3-7 days).
  4. Plot: r^2 (y axis) vs window length (x axis)
  5. Identify the r^2 (and the corresponding window length) that is on the cusp of plateau line in plot
  6. Plot: time series of moving average with window corresponding to r^2 in step 5
